This paper discusses the use of TLS proxies for both benevolent and malicious purposes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The measurement tool used in the study involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE) aspects. The paper also touches on user privacy and transparency, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI) and cybercrime (cs.CY).
